hugetlb: Fix possible deadlock

This commit attempts to fix a deadlock by explicitly releasing resv->lock in
the error path of region_chg when allocate_file_region_entries fails.

> diff --git a/mm/hugetlb.c b/mm/hugetlb.c
> index d6ea11113f1d..230fd8c63588 100644
> --- a/mm/hugetlb.c
> +++ b/mm/hugetlb.c
> @@ -807,8 +807,10 @@ static long region_chg(struct resv_map *resv, long f, long t,
>  	if (*out_regions_needed == 0)
>  		*out_regions_needed = 1;
>  
> -	if (allocate_file_region_entries(resv, *out_regions_needed))
> +	if (allocate_file_region_entries(resv, *out_regions_needed)) {
> +		spin_unlock(&resv->lock);

Can this cause a double-unlock on resv->lock?

Looking at allocate_file_region_entries, the function drops resv->lock before
entering the allocation loop:

static int allocate_file_region_entries(struct resv_map *resv,
					int regions_needed)
{
[ ... ]
		spin_unlock(&resv->lock);
		for (i = 0; i < to_allocate; i++) {
			trg = kmalloc_obj(*trg);
			if (!trg)
				goto out_of_memory;
			list_add(&trg->link, &allocated_regions);
		}
[ ... ]

If the kmalloc_obj allocation fails, it jumps to the out_of_memory label and
returns -ENOMEM without ever reacquiring the lock:

out_of_memory:
	list_for_each_entry_safe(rg, trg, &allocated_regions, link) {
		list_del(&rg->link);
		kfree(rg);
	}
	return -ENOMEM;
}

Since allocate_file_region_entries returns with the lock already released in
the error path, does adding spin_unlock(&resv->lock) here result in unlocking
it a second time?

>  		return -ENOMEM;
> +	}
>  
>  	resv->adds_in_progress += *out_regions_needed;
>

